The paper proposes a deep learning approach for image reconstruction from sub-sampled RF data in ultrasound imaging systems. This involves utilizing redundancy in the Rx-Xmit plane to interpolate missing data. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV) as it deals with image processing and analysis. The paper also involves the use of deep learning algorithms, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) categories. Additionally, the paper involves multimedia (cs.MM) as it deals with ultrasound imaging systems. Finally, the paper involves neural networks (cs.NE) as it proposes a deep learning approach for image reconstruction.
